President Obama thanks Mike Boots for his service as one of his top environmental advisors, particularly his leadership of the Council on Environmental Quality. Boots' tenure has coincided with significant progress on climate change and conservation. His expertise and collaboration with local leaders have guided the President's actions to strengthen infrastructure and address climate change threats. Under Boots' leadership, the President fulfilled his pledge to protect environmentally and culturally significant areas by permanently preserving over 260 million acres as national monuments. President Obama acknowledges the positive impact of Boots' contributions and wishes him well in his future endeavors.